showed.text: The \emph{chordality} of a graph $G=(V,E)$ is defined as the minimum $k$ such that we can write $E=E_1,\cap\dots\cap E_k$ with each $(V,E_i)$ a chordal graph.
Corollary 4. For any graph $G$, $\mathrm{Chord}(G) \le \chi(G)$, the chromatic number of $G$.
